<subSubSection lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1844,2013]" lastBlockId="33.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,1844,1869]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notes</emphasis>
. The genus was hitherto composed of five species from India and Myanmar. Here we transfer one more species to the genus and report the genus for the first time from Thailand. Members of this genus are easily separated from other similar genera (
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gunther" authorityYear="1938" box="[585,728,1916,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Euscelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[585,728,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Euscelimena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[790,905,1916,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[790,905,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Scelimena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the smaller and robust appearance, blunt (obtuse) pronotal projections and obtuse femoral teeth, usually bright yellow or orange (Günther 1938, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref35809" refString="Blackith, R. E. (1992) The Tetrigidae (Insecta; Orthoptera) of South-East Asia; an Annotated Catalogue with Partial Translated Keys and Bibliography. Japaga Press, Dublin, LIV + 249 pp." type="book">Blackith 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, species of this genus lack teeth on the ventral margin of the hind femora. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893)" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" baseAuthorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Indoscelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birmanica">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Indoscelimena birmanica</emphasis>
(Brunner von 
<bibRefCitation box="[437,631,151,176]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref36147" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K. (1893) Revision du systeme des Orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Leonardo Fea de Birmanie. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 13 (33), 1 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5121" type="journal article">Wattenwyl, 1893</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Myanmar and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[880,963,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Indoscelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="india" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[880,963,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">I. india</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[972,1102,151,176]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[972,1102,151,176]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[1120,1204,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1752,1774]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,1084,1723]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,1076,1731]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 12. Male of Indoscelimena india (Hancock, 1907) comb. nov. from northeastern India. Photograph by Hojun Song, reproduced with photographer's permission. Scale bar 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437983/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1907" authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="india">
<emphasis box="[1254,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Scelimena india</emphasis>
Hancock, 1907
</taxonomicName>
could be synonymous, but more material is needed. Accurate delimitation of this genus from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[151,266,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,266,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Scelimena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still needed, because some species have overlapping morphology between two genera, including 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hancock, 1915)" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1915" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S. discalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[254,430,260,285]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref37380" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1915) V. Indian Tetriginae (Acrydiinae). Records of the Indian Museum, 11, 55 - 137." type="journal article">Hancock, 1915</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo, 2018" authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" box="[500,677,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gombakensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[500,677,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S. gombakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[687,781,260,285]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[687,781,260,285]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
This is one of the rather neglected genera and since its establishment, not revision was published. Thus, we do not preform revision of the genus, but point the necessity for it in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
